Disavowed and disbanded, the unit is restored to track down a notorious terrorist after a brutal prison break. Tasked with covert military intelligence and high-risk operations, the resurrected Section 20 embarks on a lethal manhunt that will uncover a vast web of interconnected criminal activity. As the team journeys across the Middle East and Europe, it uncovers a deadly conspiracy that threatens to change the face of modern warfare forever.
Stonebridge, Scott and the rest of the team sign up for another do-or-die trying adventure when the daughter of Thailand's British ambassador is kidnapped.

The third series of "Strike Back", subtitled Shadow Warfare, finds the Section 20 operatives going on the hunt for international terrorist al-Zuhari and his minions, which puts them in the line of fire in locations around the world including much of Europe, Colombia, and Beirut. Sullivan Stapleton returns in the role of the once-disgraced agent Damian Scott. Dougray Scott guest stars as a shady agent who has insider knowledge about al-Zuhari.

Scott & Stonebridge scour Africa in pursuit of a fresh covey of criminals--each vying for possession of a box of valuable nuclear-bomb triggers that could launch Armageddon--in Season 2 of the hit Cinemax series.

A high-octane, globe-spanning thriller with storylines ripped from today's headlines, Strike Back is a one-hour drama series that focuses on two members of a top-secret anti-terrorist organization known as Section 20: Michael Stonebridge, a British sergeant in the ultra secret Section 20 anti-terrorist team, and Damien Scott, a Delta Forces operative who was disgraced and discharged on the eve of the U.S. invasion of Iraq. The 10-episode season follows Stonebridge (Philip Winchester) and Scott (Sullivan Stapleton) as they criss-cross the globe on the trail of a deadly international terrorist named Latif, who is planning a major attack involving a cache of WMD that could have global repercussions. Within the season-long arc involving the search for Latif (code-named "Project Dawn"), five separate adventures will be presented, each played out over two episodes. Sexy, suspenseful and action-packed, the series is set in exotic locations and has an abundance of twists and turns, as the two protagonists venture into New Delhi, Cape Town, Darfur and beyond to thwart the bad intentions of terrorists intent on bringing anarchy and destruction to our planet.

Sensible Joe Hackett and his fun-loving brother, Brian, run a one-plane airline in this folksy ensemble sitcom. Their mutual friend (and on-again, off-again love interest for Joe) is Helen, who works the lunch counter while dreaming of being a cellist. Among their quirky coworkers: a dim-bulb maintenance man and Tony Shalhoub's Italian-immigrant cabbie. The series was produced by the same folks responsible for 'Cheers' and had a nice seven-year run.

Hosted by John Heilemann (NBC/MSNBC, Game Change,), Mark McKinnon, and Alex Wagner (CBS News and The Atlantic), who joins the show as a permanent host this season, THE CIRCUS will continue to provide viewers with the same fast-paced, real-time, backstage perspective and eye-catching production qualities for which the show has been celebrated. In the year ahead, the series will explore the stories behind the headlines and pull back the curtain on the behind-the-scenes drama unfolding in Washington and across the country in the run-up to the most consequential mid-term elections in our lifetimes.

The groundbreaking real-time political documentary series about America's presidential campaign returns, examining the unprecedented events unfolding in Donald Trump's administration. Journalists Mark Halperin and John Heilemann take the pulse of the country beyond the beltway while pulling back the curtain on a White House unlike any that has come before.  -- (C) SHOWTIME

An ensemble comedy that centers on a support group for alien abductees and the skeptical journalist investigating them.

TBS's sci-fi comedy series follows Ozzie Graham (Wyatt Cenac), a journalist who is assigned to cover a support group for "experiencers," or alien abductees. While initially skeptical of the group's claims, Ozzie begins to further investigate the mysterious circumstances surrounding the experiencers and is soon drawn into a web of intrigue. Also starring: Ana Gasteyer, Luke Jones, Brian Huskey and Alice Wetterlund.

After an explosive entrance in the previous season's finale, rich socialite Pamela Brinton (Kristen Wiig) joins the gang of survivors as they search for a new haven in the fourth season of "The Last Man on Earth." However, Pamela turns out to be spoiled and even more annoying than Phil Miller (Will Forte), so the group attempts to ditch her. But instead of abandoning Pamela, they find Glenn (Chris Elliott) on a deserted island. While struggling to fit together in the new sanctuary they found in Mexico, the gang realize that even though they are a disaster together, they're better off staying together, especially when the mysterious Karl Cowperthwaite (Fred Armisen) shows up. Also starring are Kristen Schaal as Carol Miller, Mel Rodriguez as Todd Rodriguez, January Jones as Melissa Chartres, Mary Steenburgen as Gail Klosterman, Cleopatra Coleman as Erica Dundee, and Keith L. Williams as Jasper. Martin Short, Jack Black, Alma Martinez, and Leighton Meester make guest appearances.

Season 3 of this comedy series opens with armed intruders storming the Malibu beach near Tandy Miller's (Will Forte) home, putting the safety of the group at risk. Meanwhile, Melissa (January Jones) and Gail (Mary Steenburgen) are both in a relationship with Todd (Mel Rodriguez), but the love triangle goes through a rough patch. When the group realize that the air all over the country might be contaminated, they scramble to find a safe place to stay. Guest stars this season include Jon Hamm and Kristen Wiig.

Season 2 of this comedy series picks up right after last season's finale, with Phil (Will Forte) and Carol (Kristen Schaal) striking out on their own after Phil is banned from Tucson by the rest of the group. However, when Phil realizes that Carol misses her friends, he decides to risk his safety and return to Tucson. Meanwhile, Phil's astronaut brother, Mike Miller (Jason Sudeikis), attempts to descend to Earth from outer space without human aid.

Will Forte created and stars in this post-apocalyptic comedy about a man named Phil Miller, who suspects he's the sole survivor after a deadly virus sweeps the planet in 2020, a feeling seemingly confirmed when he searches in vain all over the U.S., Canada and Mexico in his RV and finds no one. Despondent, he returns to his hometown of Tucson to mull the future of mankind, yet his sheer loneliness drives him to contemplate suicide. Just before he's about to end it all, however, he spots smoke coming from a campfire that belongs to—a woman named Carol (Kristen Schaal)! The series also stars January Jones, Mel Rodriguez, Cleopatra Coleman, Mary Steenburgen, Boris Kodjoe and Jason Sudeikis.

Former river police officer John Marlott (Sean Bean) escapes from Bedlam and changes his identity to seek revenge on the person who framed him and destroyed his career and reputation. However, a new series of murders threatens his allies and sidetracks him from his path of vengeance. A stranger named Frederick Dipple (Laurence Fox) leaves him clues that open opportunities for Marlott to stop the recent murders and restore his own good name. Ed Stoppard and Vanessa Kirby return for the second season of "The Frankenstein Chronicles" as the siblings Lord Daniel and Lady Jemima Harvey, as do Tom Ward as Sir Robert Peel, Robbie Gee as Billy Oates, and Richie Campbell as Joseph Nightingale. Joining the cast are Maeve Dermody as Esther Rose, Guy Henry as the Dean of Westminster, Andrew Havill as Reverend Ambrose, Paul Kennedy as Inspector Treadaway, Martin McCann as Renquist, and Lily Lesser as Ada Byron.

What started as an undercover operation to bust drug trafficking across the River Thames turns into something more gruesome when Inspector John Marlott (Sean Bean) finds a patched-up body on the riverbank. His discovery attracts the attention of renowned surgeon Sir William Chester (Samuel West) and Her Majesty's Home Secretary Sir Robert Peel (Tom Ward), who task him to solve the case as quickly and quietly as possible so it won't derail their political agenda. As Inspector Marlott delves more deeply into the mystery of the patchwork corpse, he finds that he may have uncovered a secret best left alone. The first season of "The Frankenstein Chronicles" also stars Ed Stoppard and Vanessa Kirby as the siblings Lord Daniel and Lady Jemima Harvey, Elliot Cowan as Sir Bentley Warburton, Robbie Gee as Billy Oates, Richie Campbell as Joseph Nightingale, Steven Berkoff as William Blake, and Anna Maxwell Martin as Mary Shelley.
